deduce that the product cannot be uniquely generated there for we must produce a list
of quadruples which contain no quadruples with unique products.

2. Number of elements in the list binding Q after executing s2(Q,100) is 145.
After sentence (b) is announced we can deduce that the sum of X and Y
cannot produce a unique product. Therefore we can eliminate any quadruples
from the list that has a sum which gives a unique product


3. Number of elements in the list binding Q after executing s3(Q,100) is 86.
